&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;4&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;i.e.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;the potential terminating&amp;nbsp;of the chief financial officer&amp;rsquo;s contract.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in option &lt;strong&gt;4&lt;/strong&gt;, specifically in the phrase &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;the potential terminating.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;terminating&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is a gerund, and it does not fit correctly in this context to describe a hypothetical action.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct usage should be &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;the potential termination&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;, where &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;termination&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is a noun that aligns with the sentence structure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The committee members were instructed to carefully and thoroughly examine every single discrepancy found within the internal ledger before they submitted their final recommendation regarding the potential &lt;strong&gt;termination &lt;/strong&gt;of the chief financial officer&amp;rsquo;s contract&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grammatical Tip:&lt;/strong&gt; When describing a hypothetical or formal action, use a proper noun instead of a gerund to maintain grammatical accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correction aligns with formal writing conventions, which prioritize clarity and correctness in professional contexts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Something that will never happen&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s understand the meaning and usage of the given idiom:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;When hell freezes over:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;used to say that one thinks that something will never happen&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;He&amp;#39;ll apologize when &lt;strong&gt;hell freezes over&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(68, 68, 68);   &quot;&gt;This expression was first used in the 19th Century, Middle American English. It states an universal fact&amp;nbsp;describing hell as a place that would remain hot for all of eternity.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;To consult together&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The idiom, &lt;strong&gt;To put heads together&lt;/strong&gt; means&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;consult and work together.&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;/span&gt;परामर्श करें और एक साथ काम&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(77, 81, 86);  &quot;&gt;करना)&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For example-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt; Students should put their heads together to solve this problem.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 2&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;navigate&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage highlights the role of ethical leadership in public administration and how administrators must handle competing interests and pressures responsibly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence states that a principled administrator must &lt;strong&gt;_____ these pressures without compromising core values&lt;/strong&gt;, implying the ability to manage or deal with difficult situations wisely.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;navigate&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to carefully manage or steer through complex situations or challenges, which fits the context appropriately.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options such as &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;evade&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;amplify&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;intensify&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; do not logically express the idea of responsibly handling pressures.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Evade (बचना / टालना):&lt;/strong&gt; It means to escape or avoid something, especially a responsibility or problem. This does not fit because an administrator should manage pressures, not avoid them.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amplify (बढ़ाना / तीव्र करना):&lt;/strong&gt; It means to increase the strength, volume, or importance of something. This does not fit the context of handling pressures.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Intensify (तेज़ करना / बढ़ाना):&lt;/strong&gt; It means to make something stronger or more extreme, which is opposite to the intended meaning in the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage discusses the importance of &lt;strong&gt;ethical leadership and accountability in public administration&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;It states that corruption and favoritism can weaken public trust, so institutional safeguards are created to control misuse of authority.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;curtail&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means &lt;strong&gt;to reduce, limit, or restrict something&lt;/strong&gt;, which fits the context of limiting the arbitrary use of power.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options such as &lt;strong&gt;encourage, justify, and conceal&lt;/strong&gt; do not logically fit because safeguards are meant to control or restrict power, not promote or hide it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Encourage (प्रोत्साहित करना):&lt;/strong&gt; To support or promote something. It does not fit the context because safeguards are not meant to promote misuse of power.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Justify (औचित्य सिद्ध करना):&lt;/strong&gt; To show that something is reasonable or acceptable. This does not suit the context of controlling arbitrary power.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conceal (छिपाना):&lt;/strong&gt; To hide something. Institutional safeguards are meant to prevent misuse, not hide it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 1&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage discusses &lt;strong&gt;ethical leadership in public administration&lt;/strong&gt; and the importance of maintaining integrity and accountability.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence states that leaders must show moral courage to ______ wrongdoing, even when it is politically inconvenient.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;confront&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to face, challenge, or deal with a difficult situation directly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Thus, ethical leaders should &lt;strong&gt;confront wrongdoing&lt;/strong&gt; rather than ignore it, which fits logically and contextually in the passage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 1&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Endorse&lt;/strong&gt; (समर्थन करना): To publicly support or approve something; it does not fit because ethical leaders should oppose wrongdoing, not support it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tolerate&lt;/strong&gt; (सहन करना): To allow something unpleasant without opposing it; this contradicts the idea of moral courage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overlook&lt;/strong&gt; (नज़रअंदाज़ करना): To ignore or fail to notice something; ethical leadership requires addressing wrongdoing rather than ignoring it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 1&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage explains how ethical and empathetic leadership helps strengthen trust between government authorities and citizens.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence states that administrators who understand the socio-economic realities of citizens can design inclusive policies that help reduce the gap between the government and the public.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;bridge&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to connect or reduce the distance between two groups or ideas, which fits the context of reducing the gap.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Thus, the phrase &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;bridge the gap&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; correctly conveys the idea of improving understanding and cooperation between authorities and citizens.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 1&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Widen (चौड़ा करना):&lt;/strong&gt; Means to increase the distance or difference between two things, which is opposite to the intended meaning in the passage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Obscure (अस्पष्ट करना):&lt;/strong&gt; Means to make something unclear or difficult to understand; it does not fit the context of improving connection between citizens and government.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Distort (विकृत करना):&lt;/strong&gt; Means to twist or misrepresent information or reality; it does not logically fit with the idea of improving relations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 3&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage discusses ethical leadership in public administration and the negative effects of bureaucratic inertia and complacency on governance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence states that complacency and bureaucratic inertia can ______ reform initiatives, which then leads to delays in essential services and frustration among citizens.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Impede&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to hinder, obstruct, or slow down progress, which fits logically with the idea of delaying reforms and services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Thus, the word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;impede&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; appropriately completes the sentence by conveying the idea of obstructing or slowing reform initiatives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 3&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expedite (तेज़ करना):&lt;/strong&gt; It means to speed up or accelerate a process. This contradicts the context of delays in reform initiatives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Facilitate (सुगम बनाना):&lt;/strong&gt; It means to make a process easier or smoother. This does not fit the negative context described in the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Initiate (आरंभ करना):&lt;/strong&gt; It means to begin or start something. The sentence requires a word indicating obstruction rather than beginning reforms.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  font-weight: 700; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;Directions: In this section, each item consists of six sentences of a passage. The first and sixth sentences are given in the beginning as S1 and S6. The middle four sentences in each have been jumbled up and labelled as P, Q, R and S. You are required to find the proper sequence of the four sentences and mark your response accordingly on the answer sheet.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;S1:&amp;nbsp;There is no sound more familiar in Calcutta than the clanking of its tramcars.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;S6:&amp;nbsp;Their progress is regarded with the mixture of dread and embarrassment reserved for the approach of a cantankerous old aunt.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;P:&amp;nbsp;For a growing body of opinion in the city, trams are a symbol of urban blight.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Q:&amp;nbsp;It is also an irritant.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;R:&amp;nbsp;All day and late. into the night the trundling roll of a tram has become a symbol, a portent.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;S:&amp;nbsp;Slow, overcrowded and unwieldy, they are thought of as obstructionist and outmoded.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

